Make GiNaC::make_hash_seed() deterministic across process runs on every
platform, not just _WIN32/__APPLE__.

GiNaC::basic::compare() (used to canonically order the terms of every
sum/product, and by extension any std::set/std::map<GiNaC::ex, ...,
GiNaC::ex_is_less> pyoomph's code generator builds) sorts primarily by
GiNaC::basic::gethash(). The default make_hash_seed() hashes the *address*
of the RTTI type-name string (type_info::name()), which moves every process
run under ASLR - so the same input script can produce a differently-ordered
(but equally correct) generated C++ file on every run.

GiNaC already ships a deterministic alternative (crc32 of the mangled type
name string) behind GINAC_HASH_USE_MANGLED_NAME, but only turns it on for
_WIN32/__APPLE__. This patch turns it on unconditionally so Linux builds get
reproducible code generation too. See pyoomph branch deterministic_codegen.

--- a/ginac/hash_seed.h
+++ b/ginac/hash_seed.h
@@ -8,9 +8,20 @@
 #include <typeinfo>
 #include <cstring>
 #include "utils.h"
-#if defined(_WIN32) || defined(__APPLE__)
+// pyoomph: always use the mangled-name (CRC32) hash seed below, on every
+// platform, instead of only on _WIN32/__APPLE__. The alternative path hashes
+// the *address* of the RTTI type-name string, which shifts every process run
+// under ASLR. Since GiNaC::basic::compare() sorts primarily by hash, that
+// makes the term order of every sum/product - and the iteration order of any
+// std::set/std::map<GiNaC::ex, GiNaC::ex_is_less> built on top of GiNaC types
+// (pyoomph's code generator builds several) - non-deterministic across
+// separate runs of the exact same input, even though it is perfectly
+// self-consistent within one run. The mangled name string itself is stable
+// across runs of the same binary, so hashing it instead makes code generation
+// reproducible. Cost: one CRC32 over a short (~10-60 byte) string, computed
+// once per node the first time its hash is requested and cached afterwards
+// (status_flags::hash_calculated) - not a per-comparison cost.
 #define GINAC_HASH_USE_MANGLED_NAME 1
-#endif

 #ifdef GINAC_HASH_USE_MANGLED_NAME
 #include "crc32.h"
